    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10901/84.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Russian Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d489fn1">Pouren was discharged from custody by the
                        extradition commissioner in New York City on Mar. 29, 1909.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russian Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 28.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to a memorandum
                    handed at the Department of State on January 18 and confirming my oral
                    communication made day before yesterday, I have the honor to inform your
                    excellency that on the 27th instant I received from the ministry of foreign
                    affairs a telegram advising me that the additional documents required in the
                    Pouren case, referred to in the aforesaid memorandum, were mailed on that day
                    from St. Petersburg.</p>
                <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rosen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
